ROSTOV-on-don, Russia – Russia and Uruguay progressed to the World Cup knockout rounds on Wednesday. This is after the South Americans beat Saudi Arabia 1-0, ending any hopes for the Saudis or Mohamed Salah's Egypt. READ: Salah disappoints as Egypt crushed by Russia Luis Suarez broke the deadlock midway through the first half on his 100th international appearance. The Saudis failed to find an equaliser, slipping to their second straight defeat. AFP